                <td class="statText">
                 <table>
                  <tr>
                   <td class="statText" colspan="2">
                    Heat death could arrive in as little as 2 microseconds, if energy flows twice from the third location to the first location.  On the other hand, if energy first flows from the third location to the second location, then from the third location to the first location, and finally from the second location to the first location, heat death can be put off for a total of 3 microseconds.
(Other sequences may also achieve the maximum.)
                   </td>
                  </tr>
